. (
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E39FFFF96470557FE5A4259" box="[344,457,1801,1826]" captionStart="FIGURES 107 – 115" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[233,1331,520,1797]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[221,1345,517,1815]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 107 – 115. Abdomen, ventral. Note the lanterns and posterior margin of abdominal sternite V and VIII. 107 Amydetes agnita. 108 A. apicalis. 109 A. discissa. 110 A. fastigiata. 111 A. fucata. 112 A. lucioloides. 113 Amydetes solaris sp. nov.. 114 Amydetes goiana sp. nov.. 115 Amydetes manezinha sp. nov.. Scale. 1 mm. AS VI = abdominal sternite VI. AS VII = abdominal sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252113/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Figs. 113</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E39FFFF96C30554FD9B4259" box="[476,520,1802,1826]" captionStart="FIGURES 125 – 133" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[238,1332,458,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[233,1354,437,1885]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 125 – 133. Pygidium, dorsal. 125 Amydetes agnita. 126 A. apicalis. 127 A. discissa. 128 A. fastigiata. 129 A. fucata. 130 A. lucioloides. 131 Amydetes solaris sp. nov.. 132 Amydetes goiana sp. nov.. 133 Amydetes manezinha sp. nov.. Scale. 500 µm. A. Anterior, P. Posterior" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252115/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">131</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E39FFFF95050557FDEE4259" box="[538,637,1801,1826]" captionStart="FIGURES 172 – 183" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1642,1665]" captionTargetBox="[262,1328,461,1614]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[245,1341,445,1621]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 172 – 183. Terminalia. FIGURES 172, 176 and 180 syntergite (dorsal) and abdominal sternite (ventral). FIGURES 173 – 175, 176 – 178, 180 – 182 Aedeagus (dorsal. 172, 176, 180. ventral. 173, 177. 181. lateral. 174, 178, 182). FIGURES 172 – 175 Amydetes solaris sp. nov.. 176 – 179 Amydetes goiana sp. nov.. 180 – 183 Amydetes manezinha sp. nov. Scale. 200 µm. VP = ventral plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252120/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
172– 
